<div class="page-header">
  <p class="page-back-link mb-1">
    <%= link_to dashboard_path, class: "link-back" do %>
      <span class="link-back-arrow" aria-hidden="true">←</span> Back to dashboard
    <% end %>
  </p>
  <h1>How to use</h1>
  <p class="page-subtitle">Get started with ThesisTrack in a few steps.</p>
</div>

<div class="landing-how-to-use-grid">
  <div class="landing-how-to-use-block card">
    <h3>Students</h3>
    <ol class="landing-how-to-use-steps">
      <li>Sign up and add your supervisor’s email when prompted.</li>
      <li>Create your project with a title and description from your dashboard.</li>
      <li>Use the project tabs to manage tasks, meetings, messages, and documents.</li>
      <li>Upload documents and request feedback; your supervisor can comment on specific sections.</li>
      <li>Mark phases complete as you progress; keep an eye on deadlines and messages.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
  <div class="landing-how-to-use-block card">
    <h3>Supervisors</h3>
    <ol class="landing-how-to-use-steps">
      <li>Sign up as a supervisor; students can then select you when they register.</li>
      <li>Use the dashboard to see all your supervisees and risk flags.</li>
      <li>Open each project to manage tasks, schedule meetings, and send messages.</li>
      <li>Give feedback on documents and acknowledge messages to keep communication clear.</li>
      <li>Use the Risk dashboard and activity flags to prioritise follow-ups.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</div>
